23/05/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Macedonian Justice Minister Ixhet Memeti met his Slovenian counterpart, Zdenka Cerar, on Friday (21 May).
They discussed issues of bilateral co-operation and Euro-Atlantic integration and agreed that the two counties shared common views on EU and NATO membership.
Also on Friday, Macedonian Foreign Minister Ilinka Mitreva met with the chairman of the Italian Parliament's Foreign Policy Committee, Gustavo Selva.
Following the talks, it was announced that Italy would adopt a resolution supporting the NATO efforts of Albania, Croatia and Macedonia.
(MIA, STA - 21/05/04)
